[agent-assisted] The developer wanted to automate the release process for gitlore so users could install it via Homebrew without manual steps. CI now runs vet and tests on every push, and tagging a version automatically builds cross-platform binaries, creates a GitHub release, and pushes a Homebrew formula to the tap repository. The release pipeline requires a one-time manual setup: creating a GitHub PAT with write access to the tap repo and adding it as a repository secret before the first tag push will succeed.
